args:
Saiga takes out the Mukuroshu necromancer.
Having learned he was deceived by the group,
Saiga asks Yachiyo to strike him down as
revenge for her grandfather's life. But she
responds that the Mukuroshu is the true
enemy, and commands him to help her.
*pant* *pant* Uh oh...\nThings are going sideways again...
You fought well, but Saiga is already\ndefeated and you are near exhaustion.
However, in recognition of your efforts,\nI will spare your life if you hand over the\nscroll to me here and now.
You sure love to hear your gums flap,\ndon't ya, pal?
Ain't no way I'd ever trust some schmo\nwhose idea of a good time is hauling\ncorpses up outta the dirt.
And what harm is there in my actions?\nThe dead do not feel or think, which makes\nit acceptable to use them to my ends.
I ain't forking over the Underworld Key\nto a red hot what thinks like that.

At least my tactless brother-in-law wants it
for a good reason. You're just some goon
with no sense of respect or decency
toward the dead!
Ah, I think I see our issue now: I realize I\nhave not told either of you the full truth.
You know the Underworld Key is required\nin order to access the Realm of the Dead...
However, even if the gates ARE opened,\nthe souls of the dead can never return.\nThat part was all a lie.
I thought I was quite clear, but very well.\nEven if I open the Realm of the Dead,\nyour brother will never see his wife again.
Was laboring under a deception all along!\nHe was puppeted by a lie, and even went\nso far as to slaughter his own teacher.
He is, in my own humble words,\na fool of the highest order.
Get the hell out of my way!
Aaaah ha ha ha ha! I know that face!\nIt's the same one Saiga made when he\nrealized he had killed his own teacher!
Just thinking of it now makes me laugh!\nThe foolishness! The idiocy! How could\none NOT take joy in such high comedy?!
No! Move! Outta my way, ya jerks!\nI'm gonna take that cat's head with my\nown hand and mount it on my mantle!
Will you never learn? No matter how\nprodigious your skill at swinging that\nsword, you'll never touch me with it!
Aw, applesauce... Is this how it ends...?
If it helps, know that I will make effective\nuse of your corpse. Do say hello to Saiga\nin the next life for me, won't you?
The only one leaving this life is you.
Saiga... It can't be... You feigned death\njust for a chance to strike me...?
I knew any attempt to fight you fairly\nwould be blocked by your corpse army.
So you shot me in the back...\nlike a common craven...
A label I can live with; there is no need\nwhatsoever to engage a blackguard\nlike you on honorable grounds.
With that man laid low, the animated\ncorpses are stilled once more.
If you were just playing possum there,\nthat means you heard everything he said\nabout the Underworld Key.
Yes, I have been deceived all along.\nAnd he is correct: I am a great fool.
All these years, I have lived for the dream\nof seeing Momoyo again. But now I\nunderstand it was all for naught.
Momoyo's soul will not be be visited upon\nme—which is well and good, as the man\nI am is not fit to lay eyes upon her.

I cast aside righteousness and participated
in the foul deeds of the Mukuroshu. And
to crown it all, I murdered my teacher—
and your grandfather.
But you never planned to do all that,\nand I know it.
Kill me, Yachiyo. Strike me down.
I took your grandfather's life; now you\nmust take up your sword and have revenge.
And what good comes of that, huh?\nDon't be a sap!
Please, Yachiyo. I am so very weary.

You've been nothin' but a selfish cad since
you first darkened my door, and now you
wanna go and kick off so you can leave all
the heavy lifting to ME?!
You made a mistake, and it's on you to\nstand it like a man and make it right!

You may have bumped off Grandpappy,
but I know that wasn't what you set out to
do when this whole crazy carnival started.
It can't be! ...Tell me it can't.

...It was a frigid winter's day, the kind that
settles right into your bones. In the employ
of the Mukuroshu as an assassin, I made
my way to my latest target.

Normally, they don't specify the method by
which someone should be assassinated.
However, for that one job, they decreed
it should be poison.
I suspect now this was to ensure I would\nnot realize the target was my own teacher.
He was staying at an inn on his way to\nanswer a summons from the shogunate...\nand at that inn he died.
The Mukuroshu knew in advance where he\nwas staying, when he would be there...\nall of it. I was merely the vessel.
So I killed him—killed my teacher—\nwithout ever setting eyes on the man.
No way you'd have done it if you'd seen\nGrandpappy with your own peepers.
There is no excuse for my actions.\nMy teacher lies in the grave by my hand;\nthat is all.
Maybe, but you ain't the one what pulled\nthe strings here. That's the Mukuroshu.

No more hemming and hawing, pal!
You're going to help me avenge him
properly and fulfill his dearest ambition,
and I won't hear no guff about it!

You cast away righteousness? Fine!
I'll pick it up for ya! You've fallen from
the path? Fine! I'll grab ya by the scruff
and drag your fool butt back!
If you truly love my sister and want to\natone for what you did, then I order you to\nstop all this malarkey and come with me!
You speak of the stipulation of our duel—\nthe one where I must obey a single\ncommand from you without hesitation.
Then I have no choice. I will comply.\nYou have truly grown strong, Yachiyo.
'Course I have! Ya think I fought all those\nduels as some dog-and-pony show?
I'm gonna avenge my grandpappy\nand fulfill his dream...
I'll be the strongest blade wielder around,\nand you can take that to the bank!
